Kim Jong Il Inspects KPA Navy Unit  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 22 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il inspected KPA Navy Unit 189 honored with the title of O Jung Hup-led Seventh Regiment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Looking round a room dedicated to the history of the unit, he said that the once unknown quiet fishing port has turned into a modern naval port and the unit has grown to be invincible ranks with matchless combat capacity thanks to the wise guidance and meticulous care of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He highly appreciated the feats performed by the successive commanding officers and soldiers of the unit, noting that it was thanks to the devoted efforts made by them that it has grown to be a powerful naval unit honored with the above-said title. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After learning about the unit's performance of duty, he got familiar with the soldiers' training at a combined training room. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was greatly satisfied to learn that the unit has successfully built training rooms and put the training on a regular basis, preparing all the officers and men to be a match-for-a hundred stalwart fighters possessed of high combat technique and capacity, stressing that successful training is a basic guarantee for increasing combat capacity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Going round cultural and educational facilities including servicepersons' hall and an educational room, he highly praised the unit for having briskly conducted diverse political work and cultural and emotional activities after providing ample educational materials and cultural equipment to the ideological, cultural and educational centers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The whole army has dynamically conducted ideological work in diverse forms and methods, thus bringing about a signal turn in educating soldiers, he said, adding that this precious fruition is a striking demonstration of the validity and vitality of the principle of giving precedence to ideology consistently maintained by the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He highly appreciated the assiduous way the unit has managed its economic life, making the rounds of a bedroom, a mess hall, a kitchen, a wash-cum-bath house, a non-staple food store and other places of the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He had a photo session with the servicepersons of the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by KPA Generals Hyon Chol Hae and Ri Myong Su.

National Meeting Marks Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Assumption of KPA Supreme Commandership 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 23 (KCNA) -- A national meeting was held at the April 25 House of Culture Sunday to celebrate the 16th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Attending there were senior party, army and state officials, chairpersons of friendly parties, officials of party and armed forces organs and power bodies, working people's organizations, ministries and national institutions, officers and men of the KPA, officials in the fields of science, education, culture and art, public health and the press, men of merits and working people in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 KPA General Kim Kyok Sik, chief of the KPA General Staff, in a report at the meeting said that Kim Jong Il's assumption of KPA supreme commandership was an epochal event which provided a sure guarantee for the future development of the Korean revolutionary armed forces and the victorious advance of the revolutionary cause of Juche and it was a great national jubilee of weighty significance for the destiny and future of the country.  His assumption of office as head of the revolutionary armed forces made it possible for the KPA to invariably preserve its revolutionary nature as the army of the party and the leader and steadily advance through generations the Juche cause of building the army, started and led to victory by President Kim Il Sung, and for the army and the people of the DPRK to successfully accomplish the revolutionary cause of Juche by reliably carrying forward the Songun history and tradition of the Korean revolution, the reporter said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The period from the 1990s up to now occupies a particularly important place in the history of guidance over the army by Kim Jong Il who has led to victory the Juche cause of building the army in the van of the Korean revolutionary armed forces for decades, the reporter pointed out, and said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the grimmest period of ordeals the Korean revolution had to undergo, the KPA grew to be a matchless revolutionary elite army, and our country, which had been reduced to a ruined nation as it had no strong army one century ago, is now demonstrating its might as an impregnable military power which no formidable imperialist enemies dare provoke. The credit for this signal miracle goes to Kim Jong Il, a genius of military affairs who has been held in high esteem as the supreme commander. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il's Songun politics, the politics of independence and genuine patriotism, gave a birth to the June 15 joint declaration, an embodiment of the noble idea of "By our nation itself", and provided the "Declaration for the Development of North-South Relations and Peace and Prosperity", thus opening a bright prospect for the Korean nation advancing toward the building of a reunified, rich and strong country. And it markedly enhanced the dignity and position of Songun Korea in the international arena and immensely strengthened the international solidarity with the Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With his great Songun idea and energetic Songun leadership Kim Jong Il has trained the KPA to be the first standard-bearer and the main force of the Juche revolution, thus bringing about a miraculous victory in the struggle to defend socialism and build a great prosperous powerful nation and laying a solid foundation for the eternal prosperity of Kim Il Sung's Korea. These immortal exploits of his will remain long with the WPK's history of army building and the proud annals of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter stressed that all the people should dynamically wage an all-out drive to open the door for a great prosperous powerful nation without fail in the year which marks the 100th birth anniversary of Kim Il Sung and thus reenergize the economy of the country as a whole including its pilot domains and basic industries and accelerate the drive for making innovations in agriculture and the light industry so as to bring about a decisive turn in improving the standard of the people's living.

Chief of KPA General Staff on Tense Situation on Korean Peninsula 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 23 (KCNA) -- The situation of the Korean Peninsula still remains tense owing to the U.S. invariable war moves, said General of the Korean People's Army Kim Kyok Sik, chief of the KPA General Staff, in his report at the national meeting held here Sunday to celebrate the 16th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the KPA. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the facts, he said, show that the U.S. is talking about "dialogue" and "negotiation" but it is actually scheming to "destabilize" the DPRK's system by all vicious means and methods while resorting to the moves to invade the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He further said: We are paying deep attention to the fact that the U.S. mobilizes Japan and other satellite forces to persistently pursue the hostile policy toward the DPRK. If the hostile forces refuse to stop the large-scale war exercises and huge arms buildup, we will resolutely counter such actions with more powerful means.

Floral Basket to Kim Jong Il from Zhang Weihua's Family 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 22 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a floral basket by the family of Zhang Weihua, an anti-Japanese revolutionary martyr, on Saturday on the occasion of the 16th anniversary of his assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army and the 90th birth anniversary of Kim Jong Suk, anti-Japanese war hero. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Written on the ribbon of the floral basket were letters reading "We Wholeheartedly Wish the Great Leader Comrade Kim Jong Il Good Health."

Guarantee for Inheriting Revolutionary Cause of Juche Provided 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 22 (KCNA) -- Anti-Japanese woman hero Kim Jong Suk is the great mother of the revolution who had brought up her son Kim Jong Il as the son of the country to carry forward the revolutionary cause of Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was in the years of waging the hard-fought anti-Japanese warfare and building a new Korea with empty hand that she gave birth to her son and reared him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She raised her son, embracing him in the military uniform reeking with the smell of gunpowder in days of rigorous revolution. She frequently told him about the people's desire associated with the august name of President Kim Il Sung and his revolutionary activities and implanted the loyalty to the President in his mind through practical deed, thus educating him to carry forward the lineage of the Mangyongdae family. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When the President gave on-the-spot guidance to various units, she accompanied him along with her son so that her son might learn from the President's lofty popular traits and go by strictly his daily routine from childhood. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il used to go out for a morning walk together with the President every day and was told of a wide range of themes such as the Korean revolution, the world revolution, economic and military issues and stories about noted persons produced in the period from the ancient history to the modern history. In this course he cultivated his character and quality as the leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Busy as she was to assist the President, she devoted the utmost attention to letting her son possess admirable disposition and quality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She did not remain indifferent to his questions and fostered his observation and contemplative faculty on the complicated phenomena of the nature and society to the full. She also tried to raise his uncommon talent and taste for music. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She explained the President's plan for building a new country to her son so as to think everything on a national scale from his younger days. And she widened his way of thinking by letting him give mind to Mt. Paektu highest and grand in Korea when talking about mountains and cultivated his staunch stamina and grit no one can break. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are many anecdotes on her love shown for him to bring him up as the son of the people who regards simplicity as noble virtue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Indeed, her meticulous care and deep-going education helped him grow up as the Mt. Paektu-shaped person with wide knowledge and versatile talents. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Suk brought to reality the ardent desire of the Korean people who longed for the appearance of the bright star of Mt. Paektu for the rosy morrow of the country. Her feat will shine for all ages.

Revolutionary Museum in Hoeryong Renewed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 22 (KCNA) -- The Museum of the Revolutionary Activities of Comrade Kim Jong Suk, an anti-Japanese war hero, in Hoeryong, North Hamgyong Province, has been spruced up and at least 300 pieces of historic materials newly exhibited there on the occasion of her 90th birth anniversary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display at 17 rooms of the museum are propositions and photos of the three generals of Mt. Paektu, fine art works portraying Kim Jong Suk, revolutionary relics, books, newspapers and many other materials and data in chronological and thematic order. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among them are propositions made by President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il while remembering Kim Jong Suk and materials and data showing her birth and the course in which she grew up to be a revolutionary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are also many relics and data showing the revolutionary activities of Kim Jong Suk, who enhanced her reputation as an anti-Japanese war hero in the armed struggle to defeat the brigandish Japanese imperialists and devoted her all to the liberation of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Exhibited there are "A written warranty for a good citizen" carrying absolute trust of the people in Taoquanli in her, works portraying the three generals of Mt. Paektu and pictures on at least 20 trees bearing such slogans as "Oh Korea, we herald the birth of the star of Mt. Paektu" and "Let's hold Kim Il Sung, commander of the anti-Japanese guerrilla army, Kim Jong Suk, a woman commander, and the bright star of Mt. Paektu in high esteem for all ages. 1942." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The exhibits include materials and data proving the revolutionary activities of Kim Jong Suk who faithfully implemented the President's line of building a new country until the last moments of her noble life after returning home on November 25, Juche 34(1945). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are the immortal revolutionary paean "Song of General Kim Il Sung" newly exhibited in relief, newspapers dealing with the feats performed by Kim Jong Suk in founding the three services, multi-media showing her participation in the elections of deputies to the provincial, city and county people's assemblies, and photos and books showing her leadership over the foundation of Kim Il Sung University, the women's work and an emulation drive for increased production. Those materials and data more vividly prove the revolutionary activities conducted by her to realize the President's cause of building the party, the army and the state. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also on display there are photos convincing one that she always lives in the hearts of the Korean people for her exploits for the times and the revolution, and the medal of DPRK Hero and National Flag Order First Class awarded to her.

Endless Stream of People Visit Bust of Kim Jong Suk 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 23 (KCNA) -- An endless stream of servicepersons, people from all walks of life and school youth and children are visiting the bust of Kim Jong Suk, an anti-Japanese war hero, in the Revolutionary Martyrs Cemetery on Mt. Taesong in significant December marking the 90th anniversary of her birth. The number of visitors reaches over 500,000 at present. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On Dec. 22 alone, at least 100,000 people visited the bust to pay highest tribute to her. They included senior party, army and state officials, anti-Japanese revolutionary fighters, war veterans, men and officers of the three services, officials of institutions at all levels, working people, youth and students and Children's Union members. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Over the past 30 odd years after the cemetery was unveiled, the bust has been visited by more than 36 millions of Korean people, overseas compatriots and foreign friends. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The cemetery has been visited by at least 500,000 groups including KPA units, ministries, national institutions, industrial establishments, farms and schools until now. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Hundreds of thousands of overseas compatriots and foreigners have visited the bust during the period.

Visitors to Hoeryong Revolutionary Site on Steady Increase 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Hoeryong, December 22 (KCNA) -- The number of servicepersons, people from all walks of life and school youth and children visiting the Hoeryong Revolutionary Site is on the steady increase on the occasion of the 90th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The visitors laid floral baskets and bouquets before her statue at the foot of Osan Hill and paid high tribute to her. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The visitors to Kim Jong Suk's old home in Hoeryong looked round the relics preserved with good care. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The visitors to the Museum of the Revolutionary Activities of Comrade Kim Jong Suk looked round historic relics on display, recollecting the exploits Kim Jong Suk, woman commander of Mt. Paektu, performed by energetically working to implement the idea and line of President Kim Il Sung.

New Documentary Film Released
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 23 (KCNA) -- The Korean Documentary and Scientific Film Studio produced the documentary "Area around the River Tuman Associated with the Revolutionary Feats of Mother Kim Jong Suk".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The film records the historic materials and data showing the noble revolutionary life of Kim Jong Suk, an anti-Japanese war hero, in the area around the River Tuman and her immortal exploits performed during her activities there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It tells about her childhood and the course in which she grew up to be a revolutionary, through various relics in Hoeryong, including her old home in Hoeryong, the place where she received the education in patriotism against the Japanese imperialists from her father and the Mangyang ferry which she used to leave her dear native place with the determination to come back home again the day when the country is liberated. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It deals with the historical facts that Kim Jong Suk built the shore of the River Tuman and northern area of Korea into a bastion of revolution and led the para-military organizations in this area such as workers' shock brigade and para-military corps to the all-people resistance for final offensive to liberate the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also tells about the fact that after returning home in triumph, she went among the people to wisely lead them to realizing President Kim Il Sung's cause of building a new country, declining to visit Hoeryong, her native place.

New Documentary Screened
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 22 (KCNA) -- Part 1 of documentary film "Father of Soldiers" was screened at the People's Palace of Culture Saturday on the occasion of the 16th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The film tells about the deep love shown by Kim Jong Il for servicepersons during his inspection of KPA units. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He would cross over high and steep ridges in the forefront areas and go through rough sea to meet servicepersons and take warm care of their service and living. The film shows such moving scenes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Watching the film were senior party and state officials, the chairman of a friendly party, officials of working people's organizations, ministries and national institutions and working people in Pyongyang.

Pyongyang Wonsin Middle School Named after Hero of DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 22 (KCNA) -- Pyongyang Wonsin Middle School was named after Hero of the DPRK Yu Kyong Hwa and her bust was erected at the school. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After graduating from the middle school she studied at Kim Chol Ju University of Education. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In January Juche 94 (2005) she laid down her life at the age of 18 while protecting the portraits of the peerlessly great persons and saving revolutionary comrades from a critical situation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A meeting to name Pyongyang Wonsin Middle School Yu Kyong Hwa Middle School was held at the school on Dec. 21.

Huge Ancient Stone Altar Unearthed in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 22 (KCNA) -- Archaeologists of the Academy of Social Sciences succeeded in unearthing a huge ancient stone altar in Phyongryuk-ri, Kilju County, North Hamgyong Province. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was discovered at a riverside about 2 kilometers north of the ri seat. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Covering hundreds of square meters, the two-layer rectangular altar was built with stones, big or small, on a solid foundation. It is about 2.5 meters high.  Not a few stones used for building it weigh more than one ton. Some of them are 140 centimeters in length and 60 centimeters in thickness. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the northern side of the relic are three stairs and on the southern side large stone supports to prevent the stone wall from falling. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the top of the altar are six flat stones, 130-150 centimeters in length, 80-130 centimeters in width and 30-60 centimeters in thickness, each put on two prop stones, which are believed to be used for religious service. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the relics unearthed during excavation are pieces of brown earthenware, stone axe and stone arrowhead dating back to the period of the ancient times, holes of various shapes and a lot of human bones buried there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The discovery of the above-said relics and the distribution of menhir and dolmens around the altar prove that it was erected in the ancient times.

Parrots Begin to Inhabit Zoo
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 22 (KCNA) -- More than 120 parrots of six species began to inhabit the Central Zoo of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Among them there are Melopsittacus undulatus and Agapornis rosei collis. They live in Australia, southwestern part of Africa and northwestern part of Botswana. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The body length of the former is 22cm and its weight is about 40g. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The body of the latter is 15cm long, its wing is 10cm and its tail is about 4cm. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The parrots delight the working people and school youth and children visiting the zoo.    
