Winter Solstice and Folk Dish
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 22 (KCNA) -- December 22 is the winter solstice. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@It is an old custom of the Koreans to celebrate the winter solstice. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The winter solstice is the 22nd one out of the 24 seasons of a year in the lunar calendar. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The Korean people celebrate this day as a holiday, calling it "Ase" or "small New Year's Day". The night is longest and daytime shortest on the day around the year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The Korean people have made various folk dishes with new crops of the year and taken them on the holiday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Conspicuous among the dishes is red-bean porridge. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The porridge is made by the method of boiling red-bean well first and then putting rice and small glutinous rice dumplings as big as bird egg in it and boiling it again. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@It has been told that one should take glutinous rice dumplings as much as one's age for health. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The red-bean porridge is a seasonal food and health food which is high in nutritive value and good in digestion and absorption ratio. Everybody is fond of it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Families share their porridge with neighbors, deepening amity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Public service facilities also serve the hot red-bean porridge to customers.    
�@

Vietnamese Ambassador Hosts Reception
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 22 (KCNA) -- Ambassador of the Socialist Republic of Vietnam to the DPRK Le Van Cu Friday hosted a reception on the occasion of the day of the Vietnam army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were Pak Jae Gyong, vice-minister of the People's Armed Forces, general officers and officers of the Korean People's Army, officials concerned, diplomatic envoys of various countries and military attaches of foreign embassies here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were staff members of the Vietnam embassy here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made there.

Japan's Apology for Sexual Slavery Demanded
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 23 (KCNA) -- Some days ago, the European Parliament adopted a resolution urging the Japanese government to officially admit Japan's forced drafting of "comfort women" committed during the Second World War and make apology and compensation to the victims and their bereaved families. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This reflected the opinion of the world community demanding the Japanese government's official apology, repentance and compensation for the past crimes related to the "comfort women" for the imperial Japanese army, Minju Joson Sunday in a signed commentary says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The world is strongly urging Japan's apology and compensation for the above-said crimes because they are the most hideous crimes against humanity which can never be tolerated. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese imperialists took away 200,000 Korean women and many women of other countries by invoking the government and military power and forced them to sexual servitude for the imperial Japanese army. This is the worst violation of human rights in the world beyond human imagination. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan, however, has not redeemed its past crimes though more than 60 years have passed since the war. Instead, it is persistently denying the crimes, obstinately resorting to the distortion of history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are not a few countries in the world which committed the war crimes, but no such a country can be found as Japan which has refused to liquidate its past crimes century after century while despicably resorting to sleight of hand to evade its responsibility. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The state-sponsored crimes should be apologized and compensated by the state in a responsible manner. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's liquidation of the past crimes is an urgent historical task which brooks no further delay in view of the gravity of the crimes committed by the Japanese imperialists and the demand of the times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries are seriously mistaken if they think that Japan's war crimes, the crimes related to the "comfort women" for the imperial Japanese army, would be buried into oblivion of history and fade out of people's memory with the passage of time and change of generations.

Tightened U.S.-Japan Military Nexus Lambasted
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 22 (KCNA) -- Aggression and plunder are the intrinsic nature of the U.S. imperialists and the Japanese militarists and their mode of existence, says Rodong Sinmun Saturday in a signed article. It denounces the U.S. and Japan for their moves to tighten their military tie-up for aggression and domination. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Citing facts to prove that the U.S. and the Japanese reactionaries have long committed aggression, war, domination and plunder, it goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They share the ideas of aggression, hegemony and national chauvinism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is their strategic aim and ambition to invade and dominate other countries and nations and conquer the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is noteworthy in their moves to tighten the military nexus is that they are pushing forward military integration in real earnest above all. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They intend to regard it as their common strategic duty and mode of operational actions to realize the integration of the U.S. forces and the "Self-Defense Forces" and expand their operational theatre worldwide. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are frantic in their moves to establish the missile defense system (MD) colluding with each other. This is a new dangerous aspect in their moves to tighten their military tie-up. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What merits a more serious attention is that they are staging madcap exercises for missile defence as part of their moves to establish the MD. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are contemplating coordinating the operation and command system and staging mobile and smooth joint operations in "contingency" through intensified joint military exercises of various forms. Frantic joint exercises of forces of various services and combined joint exercises of the U.S. and Japan now under way in Japan and its vicinity and the rest of the Pacific region are aimed to achieve the above-said purpose. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their military tie-up is mainly targeted against the DPRK. They regard the Korean Peninsula, the gateway to Asia, as their strategic stronghold and a bridgehead to conquer Asia as they have a precedent and experience of aggression of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Prompted by such common strategic aim and ambition, they desperately pursue their hostile policy toward the DPRK and collude with each other in the frantic moves for a war of aggression against it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They would be well advised to behave themselves, pondering over the consequences to be entailed by their reckless military tie-up.

Art Performance of Mansudae Art Troupe Given
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 23 (KCNA) -- An art performance of the Mansudae Art Troupe was given at the East Pyongyang Grand Theatre on Sunday to celebrate the 16th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance lifted its curtain with chorus "General of Korea".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its numbers included male vocal quartet and female duet "Let Us Sing of Our Pride in Being under the Guidance of the General", trumpet solo and chorus "Dear General, Where Are You" and chorus "My Country of Songun".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers highly sang of the undying feats performed by Kim Jong Il who has strengthened and developed the KPA into an invincible strong army, the main force of the Songun revolution, with his distinguished Songun idea and leadership to provide a powerful military guarantee for the revolution of Juche and has won victory after victory in accomplishing the cause of socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance was appreciated by senior party, army and state officials, the chairman of a friendly party, officials of armed forces organs, ministries and national institutions, servicepersons and working people in the city of Pyongyang.

Foreign Crewmen Meet to Mark DPRK's Significant Days
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 23 (KCNA) -- Meetings of foreign crewmen took place at Chongjin Port in North Hamgyong Province and Haeju Port in South Hwanghae Province on December 20 and 21 on the occasions of the 16th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army and the 90th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the meetings noted that under the wise guidance of Kim Jong Il the KPA has grown to be revolutionary armed forces firmly prepared in political, ideological and military technical aspects and the invincible combat ranks capable of wiping out any formidable imperialist aggression forces at one blow. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They stressed that the DPRK is now bringing the new heyday of building a great prosperous powerful nation while smashing the moves of the imperialists with the might of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They praised Kim Jong Suk for the immortal and great feats she performed in the struggle for the liberation of the country and the happiness of the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A congratulatory letter to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting held in Haeju Port. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the meetings were captains and crewmen of Belize-flagged ships and China-flagged ships.

Kim Jong Il's Feats Praised
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 22 (KCNA) -- General Secretary of the Palestinian Popular Struggle Front Khalid Abdul Majid issued a statement on December 14 on the occasion of the 16th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He in his statement said that Kim Jong Il achieved perfect unity and cohesion of the leader, the army and the people by leading the DPRK with the Songun politics based on the Juche idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The imperialists and their stooges feel fearful of the DPRK as it holds Kim Jong Il in high esteem as supreme commander of the KPA, he stressed.

DPRK's Important Days Marked in Different Countries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 22 (KCNA) -- Meetings were held in Switzerland and Poland and a seminar and film show in Pakistan on Dec.10 and 15 on the occasion of the 16th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army and the 90th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Displayed in the venues of the functions were famous works of the peerlessly great men and photos showing the immortal exploits of their Songun leadership and books and photos introducing Songun Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chairman of the Switzerland-Korea Committee Martin Lotscher in his speech at the meeting said that the DPRK has turned into a political and military power, which no formidable enemy dares provoke, under the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He praised Kim Jong Suk as a comrade-in-arms most loyal to President Kim Il Sung and mother of Korea who gave birth to and brought up the sun of Juche and an ardent revolutionary fighter who devoted her whole life to the independence of the country and the freedom and liberation of the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Slaboy January Guzowski, vice-chairman of the Central Committee of the Poland-Korea Association, and the chairman of a branch of the association, in their speeches at the meeting said that holding Kim Jong Il in high esteem as supreme commander of the KPA marked a historical event of special significance in carrying forward and accomplishing the revolutionary cause of the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The secretary of the Pakistan Committee for Supporting Korea's Reunification in a speech noted that the outstanding personality and quality of Kim Jong Suk as a great woman is an example to be followed by all the women of the world and her august name will shine forever with Kim Il Sung's Korea, Kim Jong Il's Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A message of greetings to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting held in Switzerland.

Books Praising Kim Jong Suk Authored by Japanese Published
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 22 (KCNA) -- "Anti-Japanese War Hero Kim Jong Suk" authored by Takashi Nata, representative of Japan Ehime Institute for Modern Korean Studies, and "Hymn to Commander Kim Jong Suk" authored by Noboru Kameda, representative of the Society of the Japan�|Korea Culture, were published on the occasion of the 90th birth anniversary of Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Book "Anti-Japanese War Hero Kim Jong Suk" carries a photo President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Suk had taken together greeting spring in an alien land during the anti-Japanese war, a photo she had taken during the period of small unit activities, photos showing her revolutionary activities during the period of anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle and during the period of the building of a new country after Korea's liberation and a photo of the three generals of Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The 10-chapter book deals with her activities to lead the children's corps and the young communist league and tells about what matchless bravery and self-sacrificing spirit she displayed in a number of battles after joining the Korean People's Revolutionary Army and how skillfully she conducted underground political activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also deals with facts about how she defended the idea and line of the President and protected his safety at the cost of her life, gave birth to and brought up Kim Jong Il, bright future of Korea, and how energetically she worked to build a new country after Korea's liberation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also edited in the book are pictures showing revolutionary relics related to activities of the woman commander of Mt. Paektu the author had taken while touring anti-Japanese revolutionary battle sites in the Northeastern areas of China and stories about her revolutionary career and exploits written by him.  "Hymn to Commander Kim Jong Suk" carries pictures of the three generals of Mt. Paektu, photos showing Kim Jong Suk's revolutionary career, art pieces portraying her personality as a great woman, grand monumental edifices in Pyongyang and those showing the might of the single-minded unity in the DPRK. 
 This Japanese-Korean book contains 38 pieces of lyrics and 11 articles divided into three parts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The books highly praise Kim Jong Suk's life as a heroic one of woman guerrilla commander and a noble one of outstanding woman revolutionary, calling her "paragon devotedly defending the leader" and "great mother of revolution."

