&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 23 (KCNA) -- The Brazil-Korea Friendship Association released an information bulletin on Dec. 17 on the occasion of the 16th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army and the 90th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bulletin in an article noted that Kim Jong Suk, who distinguished herself in safeguarding President Kim Il Sung, the legendary hero, brought up Kim Jong Il to be a brilliant commander of Songun for the future. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It said that Kim Jong Il has defended and glorified the sovereignty of Korea, demonstrating his august name as the great brilliant commander of Songun by creditably inheriting the cause of the President as desired by Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Through his inspection of KPA units, he has indicated the orientation and ways to strengthen it into an invincible army, it added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It stressed that thanks to his energetic inspection, the KPA is demonstrating its invincible might as all the servicepersons are united as one body of common destiny.

Kim Jong Suk's Birth Anniversary Commemorated in Mexico
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 22 (KCNA) -- The Mexican Institute for the Study of the Juche Idea issued information bulletin No. 10 with the portrait of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk carried on it on the occasion of her 90th birth anniversary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bulletin in an article said that Kim Jong Suk was a woman hero of Korea who together with President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il are highly lauded in the history of the Korean nation as the three great persons and the three generals. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bulletin introduced several slogans, which praised Kim Jong Suk as the "woman commander of Mt. Paektu" discovered in areas of northern Korea around Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The feats performed by her as a life guard and body guard commander of Kim Il Sung during the anti-Japanese armed struggle occupy a distinguished place among the exploits performed by her, the bulletin noted, adding that defending the headquarters at the cost of her life was the objective of her whole life and struggle and the highest goal of her life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The feats performed by her in the struggle for the liberation of the country and the freedom of the people will shine forever with the title of the "woman commander of Mt. Paektu" and the "anti-Japanese legendary war hero" in the history of the Korean nation, the bulletin stressed.

