 Noting that the world progressive people are highly praising Kim Jong Suk as a "legendary hero in the 20th century produced by Korea" and a "woman commander of the anti-Japanese guerrillas", he recalled that he had long decided to write a book showing her personality as a great person. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She gave a birth to the bright future of Korea and provided steady continuity to the revolutionary cause of Juche. This is the greatest feat performed by her. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
