 Noting that he wrote and published many books including "Bright Star of Mt. Paektu Shines", "Korea in the Era of Kim Jong Il" and "Hymn to the Sun in the 21st Century" carrying the personality of the three generals of Mt. Paektu as the peerlessly great persons, he said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 I will in the future, too, work hard to introduce their greatness among the world people.

Dismantlement of Concrete Wall Demanded in Nepal
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 23 (KCNA) -- A meeting for solidarity with the Korean people was held in Katmandu on Dec. 14, 28 years since the concrete wall was built along the Military Demarcation Line in Korea.
 The chairman of the Afro-Asian People's Solidarity Committee of Nepal recalled at the meeting that President Kim Il Sung worked heart and soul for the reunification of the country in his lifetime. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that Kim Jong Il has wisely led the struggle of the Korean people to implement the President's last instructions for the national reunification, he said: Positive events have been taking place in the Korean Peninsula thanks to his energetic leadership and efforts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The secretary general of the above-mentioned committee in his speech strongly demanded that the parties who built the concrete wall face up to the trend of the times seriously and pull down the wall without delay.

