&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Tokyo, December 20 (KNS-KCNA) -- A lecture was given in Tokyo on Dec. 13 under the sponsorship of the "solidarity movement not to allow the illegal and tyrannical actions of the police and prosecution " made up of human rights champions from various circles of Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Lawyer Hong Jong Su, permanent director of the Korean Human Rights Association in Japan who is chief of the center for legal protection of the life of compatriots in Japan in the lecture referred to the history of Koreans in Japan and activities of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon). He cited concrete facts to expose the recent search and suppression perpetrated by the Japanese authorities against Chongryon and Koreans in Japan, &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
